The construction of the Tria Residential Tower in the Dubai Silicon Oasis tech park will commence soon according to Deyaar, a leading local and regional real estate developer and real estate services company headquartered in the UAE. The Chief Executive Officer of Deeyar, Saaed Mohammed AL Qatami expressed his delight in this milestone which will deliver their very first luxury development in the Dubai Silicon Oasis; a community that is at the heart of Dubai’s efforts to become one of the world’s smartest cities. He explained that the Tria Residential Tower Project is a modern urban sanctuary that is designed to place happiness and health at the very forefront through the provision of the latest smart-home technology and resort-style amenities. The Deeyar Chief Executive Officer concluded by stating that the luxurious tower will be an added value to people in search of a self-sustained lifestyle community that offers round-the-clock security. The 32-storey upscale tower property project which is one of the largest residential developments within DSO will offer studios alongside one-bedroom, two-bedroom as well as three-bedroom apartment options. Penthouses and duplexes will also be available. Also Read: Safa Two Tower Project in Dubai, UAE, Launched Through this project, the Dubai-based property developer and real estate services provider, Deyaar Development PJSC, aims to take suburban living to the next level with the best-in-class fitness, wellness, and resort-style amenities. Those would include a clubhouse, a yoga pavilion, swimming pools, a gymnasium, squash and padel courts, steam and sauna rooms, and outdoor cinema alongside plenty of spaces that are landscaped.